===Etymology===
From the [[homographic]] [[w:Grammatical case|case]] endings of the [[nominative]], [[accusative]], and [[vocative]] forms of numerous [[Appendix:Latin second declension#Neuter|neuter]] {{etyl|la}} [[Appendix:Latin second declension#Neuter|second declension]] nouns.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/əm/}}

===Suffix===
{{infl|en|suffix|sort=um|plural|-a}}

# {{non-gloss definition|Denotes [[singular]] [[grammatical]] [[number]].}}

====Usage notes====
* The vast majority of words which feature this suffix also have standard ''-ums'' plurals formed by suffixation with the {{term|-s|lang=en}} plural suffix. However, in such situations, the {{term||-s}} suffix morphologically is additional to and separate from the {{term||-um}} suffix.

